      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Wiktionary}}

'''CGI''' may refer to:

==Technology==
* [[Computer-generated imagery]], computer graphic effects in films, television programs, and other visual media
* [[Common Gateway Interface]], a protocol for calling external software via a web server to deliver dynamic content (and .cgi, its associated file extension)
** [[CGI.pm]], a Perl module for implementing Common Gateway Interface programs
* Computer graphics interface, a low-level interface between the [[Graphical Kernel System]] and the hardware
* [[Compacted graphite iron]], a type of cast iron
* [[Corrugated galvanised iron]], a type of molded sheet-metal
* [[Cell Global Identity]], unique identifier of a cell site in cellular networks such as GSM and UMTS

==Organizations==
* [[California Graduate Institute]], an independent graduate school specializing in psychology
* [[Catholic Guides of Ireland]], a girl guide association
* [[CGI Group]], an information technology and business process services company
* [[Clinton Foundation#Clinton Global Initiative (CGI)|Clinton Global Initiative]], a forum created by former US President Bill Clinton to discuss global problems
* [[Coast Guard Intelligence]], the intelligence branch of the United States Coast Guard
* [[Commission for the Management and Application of Geoscience Information]], a Commission of the International Union of Geological Sciences to enable the global exchange of knowledge about geoscience information and systems
* [[Consultative Group on Indonesia]], a former gathering of donors to the Indonesian government
* [[Cuerpo Guardia de Infantería]], an Argentine police riot control service

==Other==
* [[Clinical Global Impression]], a scale to assess treatment response associated with mental disorders
* [[Cognitively Guided Instruction]], an approach to mathematics teaching and learning that focuses on students' thinking and solution strategies
* [[CpG islands]], in genetics, genomic regions that contain a high frequency of CG dinucleotides
* [[Cape Girardeau Regional Airport]], an airport (IATA airport code: CGI) in Cape Girardeau, Missouri, United States
* Corum's Genital Interaction
* Corum Goes International
* [[Corum's grievous intentions]] A film created for release in 2010 which lead to the fire of Budget Enterprise.
* Corum's got integers - a novel written by Steve Jobs in the early 1990's
* Corum Gropes India

