The English phrase &quot;common Era&quot; appears at least as early as 1708,&lt;ref&gt;
{{cite book |title=first so-far-found use of ''common era'' in English (1708) |url=http://books.google.com/books?id=D_wvAAAAYAAJ&amp;q=%22common+era%22&amp;hl=en#v=onepage&amp;q=%22common%20era%22&amp;f=false |publisher=Printed for H. Rhodes |year=1708 |accessdate=2011-05-18}}
