==Carboxyl radical==
The [[free radical|radical]] ·COOH (CAS# 2564-86-5) has only a separate fleeting existence.&lt;ref&gt;{{Cite journal|title = Infrared Spectrum and Structure of Intermediates in Reaction of OH with CO|author = Milligan, D. E.|coauthors = Jacox, M. E.|year = 1971|journal = Journal of Chemical Physics|volume = 54|pages = 927–942|doi=10.1063/1.1675022|issue = 3}}&lt;/ref&gt; The [[acid dissociation constant]] of ·COOH has been measured using [[electron paramagnetic resonance]] spectrocopy.&lt;ref&gt;The value is pK&lt;sub&gt;a&lt;/sub&gt; = -0.2 ± 0.1.{{Cite journal|title = ESR Measurement of the pKa of Carboxyl Radical and Ab Initio Calculation of the C-13 Hyperfine Constant|author = Jeevarajan, A. S.|coauthors = Carmichael, I.; Fessenden, R. W.|year = 1990|journal = Journal of Physical Chemistry|volume = 94|pages = 1372–1376|doi=10.1021/j100367a033|issue = 4}}&lt;/ref&gt; The carboxyl group tends to dimerise to form [[oxalic acid]].

