==Foreign relations==
Until recently, all Central American countries have maintained diplomatic relations with the [[Republic of China|Republic of China (Taiwan)]] instead of the [[People's Republic of China]].&lt;ref&gt;{{cite web|url=http://www.mofa.gov.tw/webapp/ct.asp?xItem=11624&amp;CtNode=1143&amp;mp=1 |title=Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Republic of China |publisher=Mofa.gov.tw |date= |accessdate=2010-04-17}}&lt;/ref&gt; President Oscar Arias of Costa Rica, however, established diplomatic relations with the People's Republic of China in 2007, severing formal diplomatic ties with the Republic of China (Taiwan).

